HOUSE music genius DJ Euphonik is going back to school.This time not to study, but to express his talent as a house DJ at his former school, St Dunstan in Benoni, Ekurhuleni.The Festival will take place on 13 May at St Dunstan College.He will be supported by some of Mzansi&rsquo;s finest, including Locnville, Rubber Duc, Crystal Park and Timo ODV.Speaking to Sunday Sun, the DJ, whose real name is Themba Nkosi, said music was his passion.&ldquo;While everyone else was at physical education, I would wrangle myself out of it to listen to music, so the event is more like ploughing back to the school that I went to,&rdquo; he said.The Apologies hitmaker continued: &ldquo;Sharing your knowledge in the industry is important. If I help and mentor someone who ends up doing better than I have, for me, it&rsquo;s motivation. Remember, why you&rsquo;re in the music industry.&rdquo;Early this year, Euphonik earned himself international recognition after his sizzling song, Don&rsquo;t Wanna Be (Your Friend) featuring MiCasa, was featured on an Australian radio station.&ldquo;At the moment, I&rsquo;m putting final touches to my upcoming album. The album is ready, just touches here and there, and listeners can expect an elevated standard to the material,&rdquo; he said.&ldquo;I feel good and am really excited because it means all the hard work is finally paying off. It also means people are noticing my work.&rdquo;